The [JIRA Requirements|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/JIRA+Requirements] document states:
{quote}
- Currently, Oracle JDK/JRE (formerly Sun JDK/JRE) is available for Windows (32-bit + 64-bit), Linux (32-bit + 64-bit) and Solaris Platforms (32-bit + 64-bit).
*Mac OS X systems are packaged with a JDK optimised for their hardware and operating systems. However, these JDKs are not supported by JIRA.*
{quote}

Since Mac OS X is not included in the [Supported Platforms|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Supported+Platforms], the line in bold should be removed to avoid confusing customers.
Additionally, no JDKs other than the ones written in the [Supported Platforms|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Supported+Platforms] are supported, so that line does not seem necessary.

